03:05.311 --> 03:06.938
while you still...

03:07.397 --> 03:08.439
Ah! (GROANS)

03:10.942 --> 03:12.860
Poor, unfortunate creature.

03:13.611 --> 03:14.612
I'm not poor.

03:14.696 --> 03:15.697
What?

03:15.780 --> 03:17.532
I might be unfortunate,

03:17.615 --> 03:18.908
but I'm not poor.

03:18.991 --> 03:19.992
Look at my necklace.

03:20.076 --> 03:21.953
That's genuine fox tooth, that is.

03:22.578 --> 03:23.579
You're alive.

03:23.663 --> 03:24.664
Of course, I'm alive.

03:24.747 --> 03:27.333
But, that's no reason to call me poor.

03:27.417 --> 03:30.086
Tell me, where is this
horrible stench coming from?

03:30.169 --> 03:32.130
Oh, you must mean the stench

03:32.213 --> 03:33.673
that ruined our crops,

03:33.756 --> 03:36.759
that rendered generations
of back-breaking labor

03:36.843 --> 03:39.470
completely and utterly useless.

03:39.554 --> 03:41.472
- That. ..
- Yes, that stench.

03:41.556 --> 03:42.765
They say...

03:42.849 --> 03:44.851
They say it comes from...

03:46.352 --> 03:49.355
(RETCHES)

03:53.192 --> 03:54.902
(COUGHING)

04:06.372 --> 04:08.416
(CONTINUES COUGHING)

04:33.316 --> 04:34.692
(ANCHOR WHIZZES)

04:46.996 --> 04:48.581
WOMAN: Oh, mother of mercy.

04:50.958 --> 04:53.377
(GROANING)

04:53.795 --> 04:55.588
(FLIES BUZZING)

04:56.798 --> 04:59.133
(LOUD BOOM)

04:59.217 --> 05:02.053
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

05:11.312 --> 05:13.022
MAN: To the shelter. To the shelter.

05:13.105 --> 05:14.315
Tell me, villager,

05:14.398 --> 05:15.817
how far is it to this shelter?

05:15.900 --> 05:17.151
Right around the next block.

05:17.235 --> 05:18.236
Hurry.

05:20.196 --> 05:21.197
It's right over here.

05:22.365 --> 05:24.283
Oh, good gracious. Help us all.

05:24.617 --> 05:26.327
The shelter.

05:26.536 --> 05:28.412
It's full.

05:28.704 --> 05:29.705
Meow.

05:29.914 --> 05:32.458
(SCREAMING)

05:44.345 --> 05:45.471
(GASPING)

05:46.806 --> 05:47.890
(SQUEAKING)

05:52.728 --> 05:55.439
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

05:56.148 --> 05:57.859
(GROANING)

05:59.193 --> 06:01.195
(GRUNTING)

06:01.612 --> 06:03.281
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

06:04.949 --> 06:07.243
(MUSICAL WHISTLING)

06:30.308 --> 06:32.560
(WHISTLING CONTINUES)

06:40.568 --> 06:42.403
Scissor smith, Scissor smith.

06:43.195 --> 06:44.196
How can you be so cheerful

06:44.280 --> 06:45.781
while your town lives in such misery?

06:46.699 --> 06:47.700
Eh?

06:47.783 --> 06:49.160
Somebody say something?

06:49.535 --> 06:51.120
I was simply wondering how you...

06:54.165 --> 06:55.333
Uh, never mind.

06:55.625 --> 06:57.793
(GASPS) Ah, a customer.

06:57.877 --> 06:59.128
Top of the morning to you.

06:59.211 --> 07:00.212
Actually, I...

07:00.296 --> 07:01.839
Right this way, right this way.

07:01.964 --> 07:03.215
Just keep that door shut.

07:03.299 --> 07:04.884
Keep that miserable smell out.

07:06.552 --> 07:09.096
Fresh sausages,
only three for a nine pence.

07:09.639 --> 07:11.766
Hmmm. Uh, no, thank you.

07:12.099 --> 07:13.267
Actually, I was wondering

07:13.351 --> 07:14.477
about that smell outside.

07:14.560 --> 07:16.062
Ah, then it's a rag you want.

07:16.145 --> 07:17.730
We've got burlap ones, flannel ones,

07:17.813 --> 07:19.148
seersucker, gaberdine.

07:19.231 --> 07:20.232
(SIGHS)

07:20.358 --> 07:21.692
Have you had your palm read lately?

07:21.776 --> 07:23.444
Had any pets who need grooming?

07:23.527 --> 07:24.946
How about some nice flint and tinder?

07:25.029 --> 07:26.656
Never know when you'll need some fire.

07:26.739 --> 07:29.200
(SQUAWKS) Fire rhymes with liar.

07:29.367 --> 07:30.368
Liar!

07:32.036 --> 07:33.162
Quiet, you.

07:33.829 --> 07:35.206
Your pet speaks very well.

07:35.289 --> 07:36.749
My pet? That's my wife.

07:36.874 --> 07:39.251
Never sell a wizard
an expired fishing license.

07:39.752 --> 07:42.004
Ah, how about some pickled camel feet?

07:42.213 --> 07:43.381
No, thank you.

07:43.673 --> 07:45.675
I just want to know where
that stench is coming from.

07:45.883 --> 07:48.177
Ah, then it's information
that you're after.

07:48.302 --> 07:50.012
- So you'll tell me?
- For a price.

07:50.179 --> 07:52.348
But, the lives of your fellow villagers
are at stake.

07:53.683 --> 07:54.684
Come with me.

07:57.770 --> 07:58.813
Look up there.

08:01.816 --> 08:03.359
Now, do you see the words

08:03.442 --> 08:05.611
"free information" anywhere on that sign?

08:07.738 --> 08:08.739
No.

08:08.864 --> 08:10.574
Try using this magnifying glass.

08:11.617 --> 08:12.618
See it now?

08:13.244 --> 08:14.245
No.

08:14.328 --> 08:15.454
Well, that's because

08:15.538 --> 08:17.373
I don't sell free information.

08:18.916 --> 08:20.876
(GROANING)

08:25.172 --> 08:26.590
Enough of this foolishness.

08:26.841 --> 08:28.718
You will tell me where
the stench comes from.

08:28.884 --> 08:30.803
- Now!
- All right, I'll tell you,

08:30.886 --> 08:32.888
for a loaf of bread and a ride on a wagon.

08:33.264 --> 08:35.307
Wagon. Squawk! Rhymes with dragon.

08:35.391 --> 08:36.517
Dragon. Squawk!

08:36.600 --> 08:38.436
Quiet. You'll give it all away.

08:38.686 --> 08:40.021
Give what away? What dragon?

08:40.104 --> 08:41.605
Nothing.
(LAUGHS MISCHIEVOUSLY)

08:41.897 --> 08:43.274
There's no dragon.

08:43.482 --> 08:44.483
Dragon, dragon.

08:44.650 --> 08:45.985
The smell comes from a dragon.

08:46.569 --> 08:47.611
Why, you?

08:47.903 --> 08:48.904
So...

08:49.030 --> 08:50.531
Where does this dragon live?

08:50.781 --> 08:52.283
Eh, nowhere.

08:52.366 --> 08:53.409
I'll never tell.

08:53.576 --> 08:55.578
You're beginning to arouse my ire.

08:55.745 --> 08:57.038
Squawk, spire.

08:57.121 --> 08:58.539
Lives on top of the spire.

08:58.664 --> 08:59.957
You mangy pigeon.

09:00.041 --> 09:01.375
I'll have you for dinner.

09:01.542 --> 09:03.252
So tell me, wise crow,

09:03.335 --> 09:04.920
where might I find this spire?

09:05.254 --> 09:06.630
You, ungrateful beast.

09:06.714 --> 09:08.257
You better keep that beak shut.

09:08.340 --> 09:09.425
I mean it.

09:11.302 --> 09:13.012
Looks like that shut her up.

09:13.304 --> 09:14.722
Beast, beast.

09:14.805 --> 09:16.348
The spire lies to the east.

09:16.474 --> 09:17.475
To the east.

09:17.808 --> 09:18.809
That's it.

09:18.893 --> 09:20.936
You've squawked your last squawk.

09:21.020 --> 09:22.021
(SQUAWKS)

09:22.104 --> 09:23.314
Get back here, you mangy...

09:23.397 --> 09:25.733
So, the spire lies to the east, eh?

09:36.327 --> 09:38.079
SMITH: Wait. Warrior?

09:38.496 --> 09:39.497
Warrior?

09:39.580 --> 09:41.999
Wait. I have something for you.

09:42.083 --> 09:43.959
(GASPING)

09:44.502 --> 09:45.586
Warrior...

09:47.129 --> 09:49.882
Do you really mean to fight this dragon?

09:50.257 --> 09:51.550
If I have to, yes.

09:52.426 --> 09:54.095
Then you'll need this.

09:55.054 --> 09:56.931
I've had enough of your bartering,
Scissor smith.

09:57.014 --> 09:58.432
This one's on me.

09:58.974 --> 10:00.184
Sheep's bladder.

10:00.434 --> 10:03.479
It'll help you breathe
up there in those fumes.

10:04.355 --> 10:06.107
(MUFFLED) Place it
over your head like this

10:06.190 --> 10:07.608
and breath calmly.

10:08.109 --> 10:09.735
If you have any small children with you,

10:09.819 --> 10:11.987
secure your own mask first,
then the child's.

10:12.071 --> 10:13.405
You will find exits located

10:13.489 --> 10:15.241
to the east and south end of the cabin.

10:15.324 --> 10:16.867
Beverages will be sewed shortly.

10:17.701 --> 10:19.537
Uh... Thank you.

10:20.037 --> 10:22.123
Just take care of that dragon.

10:22.540 --> 10:25.793
Years ago, I lost
a daughter to that beast.

10:33.759 --> 10:35.261
At the fork in the road,

10:35.678 --> 10:37.012
follow the rocky path.

10:37.596 --> 10:40.015
It will take you to the dragon's lair.

10:40.266 --> 10:41.892
Where will the other one take me?

10:42.059 --> 10:43.227
Space ace.

11:26.645 --> 11:28.314
(CRACKING)

11:35.321 --> 11:36.614
Whoa.

11:36.697 --> 11:38.282
(FLAPPING)

11:52.338 --> 11:54.757
(COUGHING)

12:04.433 --> 12:06.268
(COUGHING HARDER)

12:19.031 --> 12:20.032
(GASPING)

12:20.199 --> 12:21.408
(SIGHING IN RELIEF)

12:50.604 --> 12:53.023
(GROWLING)

13:05.119 --> 13:07.413
Oh, the pain.

13:08.831 --> 13:09.957
Oh.

13:10.416 --> 13:11.458
You can talk.

13:12.126 --> 13:13.419
Yes.

13:13.502 --> 13:14.878
(BURPING)

13:16.755 --> 13:18.674
You must help me.

13:18.966 --> 13:21.176
Yes, I will help you, dragon.

13:21.385 --> 13:23.470
I will put you out of your misery.

13:23.804 --> 13:25.639
No, wait.

13:26.015 --> 13:28.017
You don't understand.

13:28.475 --> 13:32.354
There's something inside me
that is causing this.

13:32.438 --> 13:33.605
Inside of you?

13:33.689 --> 13:35.232
Oh.

13:37.693 --> 13:39.194
(PARTS)

13:44.283 --> 13:47.119
(VILLAGERS SCREAMING)

13:50.289 --> 13:52.082
Those poor, uh...

13:52.499 --> 13:54.501
Those unfortunate people.

13:54.710 --> 13:55.711
All right, dragon,

13:55.919 --> 13:56.920
I will help you.

13:57.671 --> 13:58.922
Yes.

13:59.298 --> 14:01.133
You have to enter me

14:01.216 --> 14:05.471
and destroy whatever
is responsible for this.

14:06.513 --> 14:09.016
